data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func`, not `Expression`

Your expression-tree code **won't compile** anymore. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The new overload accepts a regular lambda, so conditionals work inline — no manual `Expression.Call`/`Expression.Lambda` needed.

---

### 2. Complex type columns — names are now uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Duplicate names get a numeric suffix.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column (data corruption risk); now they become `Street` and `Street1`.
- **Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`; now it's `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly so EF doesn't generate a migration that renames them:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin to the old (short) name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter at the end. Update your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same change to `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, `CommandScalarExecuted`, etc. — all methods on the interface got the new parameter.
